# $name

AiSOC **connector** plugin generated by `aisoc plugin new`.

## Where this lives

Connectors are run by `services/connectors`. To wire this up locally, drop the
class into `services/connectors/app/connectors/$slug.py` and add it to the
`_CONNECTOR_CLASSES` registry in `services/connectors/app/connectors/__init__.py`
(see `AGENTS.md` → "Connector platform conventions").

## Severity ladder

The AiSOC severity ladder is exactly four tiers:

```
info | low | medium | high
```

Every vendor-native ladder must collapse into this set inside `normalize()`.
Fill out the `SEVERITY_MAP` dict in `connector.py`.

## Develop

```bash
aisoc plugin validate plugin.yaml
pytest -v   # add tests under tests/test_${slug}_connector.py
```

## Publish

```bash
aisoc plugin publish .
```

See [apps/docs/docs/connectors](https://github.com/beenuar/AiSOC/tree/main/apps/docs/docs/connectors)
for the per-connector setup walkthrough format.
